id": ["mesh:D013739"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "testosterone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9869541525840759, "span": {"begin": 437, "end": 449}}], "text": "This KER refers to part of steroidogenesis that includes the effects of decreased dehydroepiandrosterone (DHEA) levels that can lead to decreased testosterone levels. DHEA is converted to testosterone via one of the intermediates androstenedione or androstenediol by 3-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase (3-beta-HSD) and 17-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase (17-beta-HSD). Therefore, effects on DHEA levels can have downstream effects on testosterone levels (Fl&uuml;ck, 2017; Naamneh Elzenaty, 2022).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:16:49 +0000 2026"}